706215f-a.text:
798-802 Park Place, south side, between Nostrand (left) and Rogers Aves. (right), showing the gardener cottage of Geo. B. Fish. It formerly stood in the middle of the block between Park and Sterling Place. In 1925 it was at the present location. It does not appear in the Brooklyn Atlas of 1929. From 1840 to 1848 it was the home of Geo. B. Fish who was successively a Railroad Agent, President of the Long Island Railroad and
Merchant.
1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
